column6: Whenever the patient is conscious and obeying the commands, pupil exam starts with asking the patient, "open your eyes" or a provider asking, "what are the pupils like?". Results of the pupil exam has the same identifiers (equal, reactive, bilateral etc and values in mm). Although most of the times, pupil exams start this way, there are some times where just the results are reported. Even in these cases, the results still contain the same identifiers.
